description.0: Shortly after Captain America lands on the roof of the Mansion, he is locked in battle with the Man-Ape. It is soon revealed that Man-Ape doesn't want Cap's head, but the head of Black Panther!
description.1: Things are looking grim for the Sentinel of Liberty. First, he's betrayed by Sharon Carter, and then accused of treachery against S.H.I.E.L.D. Will Steve manage to break this chain of bad luck? Or will he lose yet another friend?
description.2: The Red Raven! Is he Namor's new ally against the surface-men — or the greatest menace of all time?
description.4: The Surfer agrees to a Faustian bargain...with Satan!
description.6: Shady businessman Cornelius Van Lunt hires the Avengers as a demolition team for the new property he bought. The Scarlet Witch reveals her past with Van Lunt, and confesses that she has doubts about his motives with the team. Plus, Black Panther takes a civilian job as a teacher!
description.7: Captain America learns that his one-time sidekick, Falcon, is a wanted criminal. Believing this to be false, Captain America sets out to clear the Falcon's good name. But can Captain America overcome the heavy streets of Harlem?
description.8: Rick Jones helps Mar-Vell escape the Negative Zone by asking a big green giant for a big favor. Guest-starring the Hulk!
description.9: Daredevil finally finds Karen Page, and the murderous Brother Brimstone strikes! But his identity remains hidden! Can Daredevil uncover the murderer before more lives are lost?
description.10: It had to happen! The Gamma-Green Giant takes on the mighty Avengers. And in the middle of the San Andreas Fault, too! Will Earth's Mightiest be enough against the rage of the Hulk?
description.11: Iron Man and Val-Larr team up to fight their way out of the Dark Dimension. Can the two let bygones  be bygones, or will their differences prove too great for teamwork and survival!
description.14: A great wrap-up issue. See Asgard saved from destruction! See the rescue of Odin! And witness the battle between Thor and giant Surtur!
description.15: The Human Torch goes wild as he battles the Inhumans! But what has Johnny so hot-headed? This is the one you've been waiting for!
description.17: Traveling to Hollywood to look for Karen Page, Daredevil runs into the Stunt-Master! The villain has reverted to a life of crime and it's up to Daredevil to set his life straight!
description.18: From dim, dark caverns beneath the earth comes...Mogol the Mighty! Strong enough to defeat the Hulk- or to help Hulk destroy the world!
description.19: A fight to the death! Up from the seething sea, the Sub-mariner attacks!
description.21: Evil Loki now rules Asgard! Thor must do his bidding. And if that's not bad enough...Surter creates the Inferno!
description.22: It's mystery time for the FF again- and what better place than on the moon? Fantasy and suspense...as you like it!
description.24: The Kingpin/Schemer conflict comes to a head when the Schemer kidnaps Fisk's wife Vanessa.
description.25: With the Scarlet Witch trapped in the magical realm of Polemachus, the Avengers must devise a machine that will bridge the gap between dimensions. What does the evil Lord Arkon want with the Scarlet Witch?
description.26: Devastated by the apparent betrayal of Sharon Carter, Captain America dives into a rescue mission to save the famous Dr. Robert Hoskin from the Mandarin. Can the Sentinel of Liberty get over his heartbreak long enough to save the good doctor?
description.29: Will Mephisto finally make an offer Silver Surfer can't refuse?!
description.32: Another EPIC battle between two of your favorite Marvel heroes. Silver Surfer attempts to extinguish the HUMAN TORCH!
description.33: There's a new criminal in town with designs on being the top boss of the underworld. His name: the Schemer. His next target: Kingpin.
description.34: Quicksilver returns to the Avengers Mansion, but not to rejoin the team! After an initial miscommunication with Yellowjacket and Wasp, Pietro reveals that his sister, the Scarlet Witch, has been kidnapped after abusing black magic.
description.35: M.O.D.O.K. will go to any length to destroy Captain America. Captain America will do anything to keep justice and peace. Find out to see who will win in this action packed issue!
description.36: Caught between battling the galvanizing Gladiator, and saving the relationship with the girl he loves, Daredevil must make a crucial decision! But is it the right one? You be the judge, True Believers!
description.37: The Hulk is trapped in the occultist plot of a crazed cult! Will the Undying Ones be unleashed once more? But first, the Night-Crawler emerges. Doctor Strange guest-stars!
description.38: After the sudden revelation that Whitney Frost is still alive, Tony Stark embarks on a journey to find her. But after searching high and low the Iron Avenger soon realizes this no ordinary in-and-out rescue mission!  Enter the Minotaur!
description.40: The saga you never expected to read! Expect shock after shock as the Thunder God must accept the triumph of Loki in...The Fall of Asgard!
description.41: The FF take a much needed vacation! But while the happy family sunbathes in Florida, a mysterious fish-man is on the loose. Plus, will Reed Richards find the Lost Lagoon of mythic lore?
description.44: Upstaged by Nighthawk at every turn, Daredevil considers giving up his heroic identity. The public may look past him, but Daredevil can't shake a fishy feeling about the new guy in town. Is Nighthawk truly the hero he claims to be?
description.45: The Absorbing Man is back- and the Hulk's got him nailed! Or...is it the other way around? The answer'll rock ya!
description.46: The gloves are off as Iron Man takes on the Mercenary! Will Tony Stark perish in his fight against the Mercenary to protect the lovely Cheryl Porter? Find out who killed Tony Stark!
description.48: Someone or something is out to steal Thor's strength, and the God of Thunder isn't having it. Thor versus the carnage of Crypto-Man!
description.49: The Mad Thinker is back and more powerful than ever, aided by his Androids of Death! 'Nuff said!
description.51: Peter's money troubles have become too much for him to hande. As Spider-Man, he meets with a group of television executives to negotiate an appearance on a late night talk show. Coincidentally, the TV station has recently taken on a new janitor, Max Dillon, a.k.a. Electro!
description.52: The Sons of the Serpent frame Black Panther for a series of crimes in order to fuel racial tension in the city. The Avengers help their teammate out by creating an elaborate ruse against the secret society.
description.53: While Captain America contemplates his next move with Sharon Carter, Suprema, an ambitious criminal tries to take over the criminal underworld. Can Captain America fight crime and conquer love at the same time? Or will he lose everything instead?
description.55: The first EVER meeting between Silver Surfer and Spider-Man!
description.57: Canceling a date with Karen to search for villains, Daredevil finds himself trapped in an old, deadly amusement park by Mr. Hyde, Cobra, and Jester! Can Daredevil save himself from this theme park of terrors...and save his love life?
description.58: Will Bruce Banner and Betty Ross get married? The Rhino says "No!"...and so does the revenge-crazed Leader!
description.59: Iron Man! Crimson Dynamo! Titanium Man! When these three collide-death must follow! Find out who survives in this action-packed issue!
description.61: It's a Three-ring circus as Thor takes on Ulik, the Ringmaster, and the Circus of Crime! After treating a strongman as Donald Blake, Thor becomes suspicious of the ringmaster who employed the doctor's help. Will Thor be able to escape this funhouse?
description.62: A villain called Monocle! A plot to start World War III! And that's only the beginning!
description.64: When the portal of the Undying Ones opens, Namor and Doctor Strange battle the Undying One leader, to stop him from passing through to Earth.
description.66: When the villain known as the Kangaroo steals a vial of experimental bacteria, Spider-Man swings into action to save the day.
description.67: As T'Challa enters New York airspace after visiting Wakanda, he realizes that the Sons of the Serpent are back! And this time, the "Sons" are targeting prominent black citizens in New York City!
description.68: Captain America is once more brooding over his lot in life, wondering if he is doomed to live as a symbol of the American dream as Captain America, or if he can find a normal life as Steve Rogers. What path will the Super Soldier choose?
description.71: Daredevil learns that Crime-Wave has been operating an illegal gambling boat! Disguised as a thug, DD boards the boat to find a familiar face amongst a crowd of enemies. A showdown at sea no comic fan should miss!
description.72: The Leader is back- and out for vengeance! And if he can't find the Hulk, then Bruce Banner will do! A thriller of a read delivered by Marvel legends Roy Thomas and Herb Trimpe!
description.73: Tony Stark has had enough of the heroic life! Find out what happens when the wealthiest super hero quits being Iron Man, after the unbelievable comes true!
description.75: Jane Foster, kidnapped! No longer under the protection of Donald Blake, Jane finds herself vulnerable to a blackmailing scheme by billionaire Kornin Krask. Will Thor call on the power of the All-Father to save the woman he loves?
description.76: The return of the Frightful Four! And witness the mystic witchcraft of a brand new character! Agatha Harkness' first appearance.
description.78: While Peter and Gwen work out their relationship issues, the Chameleon strikes!
description.79: Rick Jones returns to the Avengers Mansion and is greeted by old friends. Scorpio, a member of the mysterious Zodiac group, attacks the Avengers before being joined by the rest of his crew.
description.80: Silas X. Cragg is obsessed with Captain America. Seeing him everywhere he turns, the mad scientist wish to create an even stronger, more fearsome super soldier to destroy the Star-Spangled Avenger. But who is worthy of such a task?
description.82: The witches' cauldron is whipping up something special for the Silver Surfer. The Abomination...reborn!
description.84: Millie enjoys an adventure under the sun in “Beauty at the Beach”!
description.85: Kitty’s heart is on the line for Jim in “Too Young!”
description.87: When Willie Lincoln discovers the location of Crime-Wave's secret base, the villain sends out an assassin, the Torpedo, to murder him. Daredevil intercepts this threat, but can't tackle the fight on his own!
description.88: The rematch that had to happen! Ol' Greenskin takes on the entire Fantastic Four- and how!
description.89: Lucifer has returned with a vengeance for the Iron Avenger! Still recovering from his heart surgery, will Tony Stark be able to faces the devil himself? Find out who serves Lucifer!
description.91: After the shooting of civil rights activist Pedro Luis Lopez, Thor springs into action...as Donald Blake! Will Dr. Blake be able to save Lopez's life before the city erupts into race riots? The Destroyer makes a less than triumphant return, leaving Donald Blake/Thor with even more on his plate!
description.92: The Great Games begin at last- and whether he wins or loses...the Thing must die!
description.95: Victory has been assured, but the life of a fellow friend has not been. Surfer must rush for help before a life slips away in his hands.
description.97: To keep his identity as the Wallcrawler safe from J. Jonah Jameson, Peter allows himself to be thrown out of a window by the Prowler...
description.98: Thanks to Kang, the Avengers are still hurtling through time. Some of the team does battle in 4000 AD, while Black Panther, Yellowjacket, and the Vision go up against the original Invaders in 1941 France!
description.99: Following his battle with the Red Skull, Captain America returns to the U.S. to patch things up with Sharon Carter. However, Nick Fury has other plans for the Sentinel of Liberty.

0.text: The Wrecking Crew has Captain America near death, with only one unlikely hero to defend him! Who will live, and who must be avenged?

2.text: The Red Raven! Is he Namor's new ally against the surface-men — or the greatest menace of all time?

6.text: The Avengers vs. the Wrecking Crew in England! Earth's mightiest heroes should go over big with the British, especially when the Wasp is hundreds of feet high!

25.text: Ant-Man's rivalry with Jack of Hearts is forgotten when Scott Lang faces every parent's nightmare! Will his rescue of his daughter blow up in his face, or will Jack of Hearts blow up in someone else's?

28.text: Prince Namor lashes out at the surface world, while Atlantis sits at the precipice of total war!

31.text: With the Sub-Mariner defeated, Atlantis turns to Tiger Shark for help escaping Krang's attacks!

34.text: Only the Hulk can stand up to She-Hulk, but their fight is tearing down everything else! Is the Emerald Avenger's only chance the hero who inadvertently set her off to begin with?

52.text: While the Avengers continue to search the globe for her, Jennifer Walters seeks the one person on Earth who can help control her transformations. Featuring the return of the most demanded Avenger of all!

54.text: At last! The warlord Krang strikes back! Plus -- the menace of Orka, the Human Killer Whale!

67.text: After all the enemies they've faced, the Avengers are falling before one of their own! Twisted by radiation, the She-Hulk has never been more savage - or more unstoppable!

79.text: The She-Hulk is gone, and Jennifer Walters is on the run! Her friends aren't sure what she's afraid of, but they'll find out!

81.text: Atlantis finally invades the surface world - time for Namor to pick a side!

84.text: Millie enjoys an adventure under the sun in “Beauty at the Beach”!

85.text: Kitty’s heart is on the line for Jim in “Too Young!”

94.text: Namor and the diabolical Dr. Doom, appearing together for the first time in years!

98.text: Spotlight on Hank Pym and Wasp!  Can they put their checkered past behind them in time to fend off the deadly Whirlwind?
